text: 19521 Chaos is a Kuiper belt object. Chaos was found in 1998 by the Deep Ecliptic Survey, with Kitt Peak's 4 m telescope. It is big at about 560 km, and bright at H=4.755. It is named after the primeval state of existence in Greek mythology, from which the first gods appeared. == Trivia == A jazz- fusion/progressive-rock band from Connecticut got their name from this minor planet. == References == * original MPEC circular 1998-X08 and the revision, 1999-V03 * AstDys * Chaos
